From 4d6463cb6b379c36c6d46208403394bfb31d20f1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@polyedge.dev>
Date: Fri, 3 Apr 2026 18:22:59 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: isolate paper traders per strategy for proper A/B
 comparison

Critical fix: both pipeline configurations were sharing one paper_trades.json
file and one bankroll. The first run would resolve trades, and the second
run would see nothing to resolve. Bankroll changes from one run affected
position sizing in the other.

Fix: each strategy tag gets its own directory under data/:
  data/paper_enriched+live/paper_trades.json
  data/paper_enriched+live+profiles/paper_trades.json

Each configuration now has:
- Independent bankroll (both start at $1,000)
- Independent trade counter
- Independent resolution tracking
- Both can resolve the same market independently

Whale profiles remain shared (data/whale_profiles.json) since they're
configuration-independent input data.

strategies/enriched_edge_detector.py:
- Paper trader directory derived from strategy_tag
- Added os import

run_pipeline.py:
- --report-compare scans all data/paper_* directories, loads each
  trader independently, merges for comparison
- --report shows all strategies or a specific one (--report enriched+live)
- Falls back to legacy data/paper_trades.json if no strategy dirs exist
---
 run_pipeline.py                      | 110 +++++++++++++++++++++++++--
 strategies/enriched_edge_detector.py |  11 ++-
 2 files changed, 112 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)

